tags.name: BCalendar
tags.description: BootstrapVue custom calendar widget for selecting dates and controlling other components, fully WAI-ARIA accessible (a11y) and supports internationalization (i18n)

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: Used to set the 'id' attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: Initially selected date value. Accepts either a `YYYY-MM-DD` string or a `Date` object

attributes.name: valueAsDate
attributes.description: Returns a `Date` object for the v-model instead of a `YYYY-MM-DD` string

attributes.name: initialDate
attributes.description: When a `value` is not specified, sets the initial calendar month date that will be presented to the user. Accepts a value in `YYYY-MM-DD` format or a `Date` object. Defaults to the current date (or min or max if the current date is out of range)

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: Places the calendar in a non-interactive disabled state

attributes.name: readonly
attributes.description: Places the calendar in an interactive readonly state. Disables updating the v-model, while still allowing date navigation

attributes.name: min
attributes.description: The minimum date the calendar will show

attributes.name: max
attributes.description: The maximum date the calendar will show

attributes.name: dateDisabledFn
attributes.description: Set to a function reference which returns `true` if the date is disabled, or `false` if the date should be enabled. See documentation for details

attributes.name: startWeekday
attributes.description: Day of week to start the calendar. `0` for Sunday, `1` for Monday, `6` for Saturday, etc.

attributes.name: locale
attributes.description: Locale (or locales) for the calendar to use. When passing an array of locales, the order of the locales is from most preferred to least preferred

attributes.name: direction
attributes.description: Set to the string 'rtl' or 'ltr' to explicitly force the calendar to render in right-to-left or left-ro-right (respectively) mode. Defaults to the resolved locale's directionality

attributes.name: selectedVariant
attributes.description: Theme color variant to use for the selected date button

attributes.name: todayVariant
attributes.description: Theme color variant to use for highlighting todays date button. Defaults to the `variant` prop

attributes.name: noHighlightToday
attributes.description: Disabled the highlighting of todays date in the calendar

attributes.name: dateInfoFn
attributes.description: Set to a function reference which returns a class (string), or classes (array of strings) to apply to the date cell. See documentation for details

attributes.name: width
attributes.description: The width of the calendar. Has no effect if prop `block` is set

attributes.name: block
attributes.description: Makes the calendar full width

attributes.name: hideHeader
attributes.description: When `true`, visually hides the selected date header

attributes.name: showDecadeNav
attributes.description: When `true`, shows the +/- decade navigation buttons

attributes.name: hidden
attributes.description: When `true`, renders a comment node instead of the calendar widget while keeping the Vue instance active. Mainly used when implementing a custom date picker

attributes.name: ariaControls
attributes.description: If the calendar controls another component/element, set this prop to the ID of the element the calendar controls

attributes.name: roleDescription
attributes.description: Sets a value for the `role-description` attribute on the component

attributes.name: labelPrevDecade
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the optional `Previous Decade` navigation button

attributes.name: labelPrevYear
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Previous Year` navigation button

attributes.name: labelPrevMonth
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Previous Month` navigation button

attributes.name: labelCurrentMonth
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Current Month` navigation button

attributes.name: labelNextMonth
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Next Month` navigation button

attributes.name: labelNextYear
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Next Year` navigation button

attributes.name: labelNextDecade
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the optional `Next Decade` navigation button

attributes.name: labelToday
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute for the calendar grid date button to signify that the date is today's date

attributes.name: labelSelected
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute set on the calendar grid date button that is selected

attributes.name: labelNoDateSelected
attributes.description: Label to use when no date is currently selected

attributes.name: labelCalendar

tags.name: BFormDatepicker
tags.description: BootstrapVue custom date picker input form control, which provides full WAI-ARIA accessibility (a11y) and supports internationalization (i18n)

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: Used to set the 'id' attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: Initially selected date value. Accepts either a `YYYY-MM-DD` string or a `Date` object

attributes.name: valueAsDate
attributes.description: Returns a `Date` object for the v-model instead of a `YYYY-MM-DD` string

attributes.name: resetValue
attributes.description: When the optional `reset` button is clicked, the selected date will be set to this value. Default is to clear the selected value

attributes.name: initialDate
attributes.description: When a `value` is not specified, sets the initial calendar month date that will be presented to the user. Accepts a value in `YYYY-MM-DD` format or a `Date` object. Defaults to the current date (or min or max if the current date is out of range)

attributes.name: placeholder
attributes.description: Text so show in the form control when no date is selected. Defaults to the `label-no-date-selected` prop value

attributes.name: size
attributes.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

attributes.name: min
attributes.description: The minimum date the calendar will show

attributes.name: max
attributes.description: The maximum date the calendar will show

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: Places the calendar in a non-interactive disabled state

attributes.name: readonly
attributes.description: Places the calendar in an interactive readonly state. Disables updating the v-model, while still allowing date navigation

attributes.name: required
attributes.description: When set, adds the `aria-required="true"` attribute on the component. Required validation needs to be handled by your application

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: Sets the value of the 'name' attribute on the form control

attributes.name: form
attributes.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the 'form' attribute on the control

attributes.name: state
attributes.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. 'true' for valid, 'false' for invalid', or 'null' for no validation state

attributes.name: dateDisabledFn
attributes.description: Set to a function reference which returns `true` if the date is disabled, or `false` if the date should be enabled. See documentation for details

attributes.name: noCloseOnSelect
attributes.description: Disables closing the popup date picker when a date is clicked/selected

attributes.name: hideHeader
attributes.description: When `true`, visually hides the selected date header

attributes.name: showDecadeNav
attributes.description: When `true`, shows the +/- decade navigation buttons

attributes.name: locale
attributes.description: Locale (or locales) for the calendar to use. When passing an array of locales, the order of the locales is from most preferred to least preferred

attributes.name: startWeekday
attributes.description: Day of week to start the calendar. `0` for Sunday, `1` for Monday, `6` for Saturday, etc.

attributes.name: direction
attributes.description: Set to the string 'rtl' or 'ltr' to explicitly force the calendar to render in right-to-left or left-ro-right (respectively) mode. Defaults to the resolved locale's directionality

attributes.name: buttonOnly
attributes.description: Renders the datepicker as a dropdown button instead of a form-control

attributes.name: buttonVariant
attributes.description: The button variant to use when in `button-only` mode. Has no effect if prop `button-only` is not set

attributes.name: calendarWidth
attributes.description: Sets the width of the calendar dropdown (see the `b-calendar` prop `width` for details)

attributes.name: selectedVariant
attributes.description: Theme color variant to use for the selected date button

attributes.name: todayVariant
attributes.description: Theme color variant to use for highlighting todays date button. Defaults to the `variant` prop

attributes.name: noHighlightToday
attributes.description: Disabled the highlighting of todays date in the calendar

attributes.name: todayButton
attributes.description: When set, shows the optional `select today` button

attributes.name: labelTodayButton
attributes.description: Content for the optional `Select today` button

attributes.name: todayButtonVariant
attributes.description: Button variant to use for the optional `select today` button

attributes.name: resetButton
attributes.description: When set, shows the optional `reset` button

attributes.name: labelResetButton
attributes.description: Content for the optional `Reset` button

attributes.name: resetButtonVariant
attributes.description: Button variant to use for the optional `reset` button

attributes.name: closeButton
attributes.description: When set, shows the optional close button

attributes.name: labelCloseButton
attributes.description: Content for the optional `Close` button

attributes.name: closeButtonVariant
attributes.description: Button variant to use for the optional `close` button

attributes.name: dateInfoFn
attributes.description: Set to a function reference which returns a class (string), or classes (array of strings) to apply to the date cell. See calendar documentation for details. Passed through to the child calendar component

attributes.name: labelPrevDecade
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the optional `Previous Decade` navigation button

attributes.name: labelPrevYear
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Previous Year` navigation button

attributes.name: labelPrevMonth
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Previous Month` navigation button

attributes.name: labelCurrentMonth
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Current Month` navigation button

attributes.name: labelNextMonth
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Next Month` navigation button

attributes.name: labelNextYear
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the `Next Year` navigation button

attributes.name: labelNextDecade
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `title` attributes on the optional `Next Decade` navigation button

attributes.name: labelToday
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute for the calendar grid date button to signify that the date is today's date

attributes.name: labelSelected
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute set on the calendar grid date button that is selected

attributes.name: labelNoDateSelected
attributes.description: Label to use when no date is currently selected

attributes.name: labelCalendar
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` and `role-description` attributes applied to the calendar grid

attributes.name: labelNav
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on to the calendar navigation button wrapper

attributes.name: labelHelp
attributes.default: "Use cursor keys to navigate calendar dates"
attributes.description: help text that appears at the bottom of the calendar grid

attributes.name: dateFormatOptions
attributes.description: Format object for displayed text string that is passed to `Intl.DateTimeFormat`

attributes.name: weekdayHeaderFormat
attributes.description: Format to use for the calendar weekday headings. Possible values are `long`, `short` (default), or `narrow`

attributes.name: dark
attributes.description: When set, gives the popup calendar dialog a dark background

attributes.name: menuClass
attributes.description: Class (or classes) to apply to to popup menu wrapper

attributes.name: dropup
attributes.description: When set, positions the menu on the top of the button

attributes.name: dropright
attributes.description: When set, positions the menu to the right of the button

attributes.name: dropleft
attributes.description: When set, positions the menu to the left of the button

attributes.name: right
attributes.description: Align the right edge of the menu with the right of the button

attributes.name: offset
attributes.description: Specify the number of pixels to shift the menu by. Negative values supported

attributes.name: noFlip
attributes.description: Prevent the menu from auto flipping positions

attributes.name: popperOpts
attributes.description: Additional configuration to pass to Popper.js

attributes.name: boundary
attributes.description: The boundary constraint of the menu: `'scrollParent'`, `'window'`, `'viewport'`, or a reference to an `HTMLElement`

events.name: input
events.description: Emitted when updating the v-model

arguments.name: date
arguments.description: Either a string in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD` or a `Date` object (if `value-as-date` prop is `true`)

events.name: context
events.description: `b-calendar` context event. Emitted when the user changes the active date via date navigation buttons or cursor control

arguments.name: context
arguments.description: The `b-calendar` context object. See the `b-calendar` documentaion for details

events.name: shown
events.description: Emitted when the picker popup has shown

events.name: hidden
events.description: Emitted when the picker popup has hidden

slots.description: Used to place custom content in the previous month navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

slots.name: nav-this-month
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the this month/day navigation button

vue-properties.name: isRTL
vue-properties.description: Will be `true` if the date navigation bar is rendered right to left

slots.name: nav-next-month
slots.description: Used to place custom content in the next month navigation button

tags.name: BFormFile

attributes.name: id

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: Sets the value of the 'name' attribute on the form control

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: When set to 'true', disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

attributes.name: required
attributes.description: Adds the 'required' attribute to the form control

attributes.name: form
attributes.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the 'form' attribute on the control

attributes.name: autofocus
attributes.description: When set to 'true', attempts to auto-focus the control when it is mounted, or re-activated when in a keep-alive. Does not set the 'autofocus' attribute on the control

attributes.name: state
attributes.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. 'true' for valid, 'false' for invalid', or 'null' for no validation state

attributes.name: plain
attributes.description: Render the form control in plain mode, rather than custom styled mode

attributes.name: size
attributes.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: The current value of the file input. Will be a single File object or an array of File objects (if multiple or directory is set). Can be set to null, or an empty array to reset the file input

attributes.name: accept

attributes.name: capture

attributes.name: placeholder

attributes.name: browseText
attributes.description: Text content for the file browse button

attributes.name: dropPlaceholder

attributes.name: multiple
attributes.description: When set, will allow multiple files to be selected. v-model will be an array

attributes.name: directory
attributes.description: Enable directory drop mode (on browsers that support directory mode)

attributes.name: noTraverse
attributes.description: For directory drop mode: returns files as a flat array

attributes.name: noDrop
attributes.description: Disable drag and drop mode

attributes.name: fileNameFormatter

events.description: original native change event on input

slots.description: Scoped slot for formatting the file names

vue-properties.name: names

tags.name: BFormGroup
tags.description: Easily add some structure to forms. Its purpose is to pair form controls with a legend or label, and to provide help text and invalid/valid feedback text, as well as visual (color) contextual state feedback.

attributes.name: label

attributes.name: labelSize
attributes.description: Sets the text size of the label: 'sm', 'md' (default) or 'lg'. Use this prop to have the label size match the form control size

attributes.name: labelSrOnly
attributes.description: Visually hides the label content, but makes it available to screen reader users

attributes.name: labelCols
attributes.description: Number of columns for the label width xs screens and up

attributes.name: labelColsSm
attributes.description: Number of columns for the label width sm screens and up

attributes.name: labelColsMd
attributes.description: Number of columns for the label width md screens and up

attributes.name: labelColsLg
attributes.description: Number of columns for the label width lg screens and up

attributes.name: labelColsXl
attributes.description: Number of columns for the label width xl screens and up

attributes.name: labelAlign
attributes.description: Text alignment 'left', 'center', 'right' for the label xs screens and up

attributes.name: labelAlignSm
attributes.description: Text alignment 'left', 'center', 'right' for the label sm screens and up

attributes.name: labelAlignMd
attributes.description: Text alignment 'left', 'center', 'right' for the label md screens and up

attributes.name: labelAlignLg
attributes.description: Text alignment 'left', 'center', 'right' for the label lg screens and up

attributes.name: labelAlignXl
attributes.description: Text alignment 'left', 'center', 'right' for the label xl screens and up

attributes.name: labelClass
attributes.description: CSS class (or classes) to add to the label/legend element

attributes.description: Text to place in the help text area of the form group

attributes.name: invalidFeedback
attributes.description: Text to show when the form group has an invalid state

attributes.name: validFeedback
attributes.description: Text to show when the form group has a valid state

attributes.name: tooltip
attributes.description: Renders the feedback text in a rudimentary tooltip style

attributes.name: feedbackAriaLive
attributes.description: Value to use for the 'aria-live' attribute on the feedback text

attributes.description: When set, adds the Bootstrap validation trigger class 'was-validated' on the component

attributes.description: Disabled the fieldset element, which in turn disables the form controls (on browsers that support disabled fieldsets). Has no effect if 'label-for' is set

tags.name: BFormInput
tags.description: Create various type inputs such as: text, password, number, url, email, search, range, date and more.

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: Used to set the 'id' attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: Sets the value of the 'name' attribute on the form control

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: When set to 'true', disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

attributes.name: required
attributes.description: Adds the 'required' attribute to the form control

attributes.name: form
attributes.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the 'form' attribute on the control

attributes.name: autofocus
attributes.description: When set to 'true', attempts to auto-focus the control when it is mounted, or re-activated when in a keep-alive. Does not set the 'autofocus' attribute on the control

attributes.name: size
attributes.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

attributes.name: state
attributes.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. 'true' for valid, 'false' for invalid', or 'null' for no validation state

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: The current value of the input.  Result will always be a string, except when the 'number' prop is used

attributes.name: ariaInvalid
attributes.description: Sets the 'aria-invalid' attribute with the specified value

attributes.name: readonly
attributes.description: Sets the 'readonly' attribute on the form control

attributes.description: Set the form control as readonly and renders the control to look like plain text (no borders)

attributes.name: autocomplete
attributes.description: Sets the 'autocomplete' attribute value on the form control

attributes.name: placeholder
attributes.description: Sets the 'placeholder' attribute value on the form control

attributes.name: formatter
attributes.description: reference to a function for formatting the input

attributes.name: lazyFormatter
attributes.description: When set, the input is formatted on blur instead of each keystroke (if there is a formatter specified)

attributes.name: trim
attributes.description: When set, trims any leading and trailing white space from the input value. Emulates the Vue '.trim' v-model modifier

attributes.name: number
attributes.description: When set attempts to convert the input value to a native number. Emulates the Vue '.number' v-model modifier

attributes.name: lazy
attributes.description: When set, updates the v-model on 'change'/'blur' events instead of 'input'. Emulates the Vue '.lazy' v-model modifier

attributes.name: debounce
attributes.description: When set to a number of milliseconds greater than zero, will debounce the user input. Has no effect if prop 'lazy' is set

attributes.name: type
attributes.description: The type of input to render. See the docs for supported types

attributes.name: noWheel
attributes.description: For number-like inputs, disables the mouse wheel from incrementing or decrementing the value

attributes.name: min
attributes.description: Value to set in the 'min' attribute on the input. Used by number-like inputs

attributes.name: max
attributes.description: Value to set in the 'max' attribute on the input. Used by number-like inputs

attributes.name: step
attributes.description: Value to set in the 'step' attribute on the input. Used by number-like inputs

attributes.name: list
attributes.description: The ID of the associated datalist element or component

events.name: input
events.description: Input event triggered by user interaction. Emitted after any formatting (not including 'trim' or 'number' props) and after the v-model is updated

arguments.name: value
arguments.description: Current value of input

events.name: change
events.description: Change event triggered by user interaction. Emitted after any formatting (not including 'trim' or 'number' props) and after the v-model is updated.

arguments.name: value
arguments.description: Current value of input

events.name: update
events.description: Emitted to update the v-model

arguments.name: value
arguments.description: Value of input, after any formatting. Not emitted if the value does not change

events.name: blur
events.description: Emitted after the input looses focus

arguments.name: event
arguments.description: Native blur event (before any formatting)

attributes.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the 'form' attribute on the control

attributes.name: autofocus
attributes.description: When set to 'true', attempts to auto-focus the control when it is mounted, or re-activated when in a keep-alive. Does not set the 'autofocus' attribute on the control

attributes.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. 'true' for valid, 'false' for invalid', or 'null' for no validation state

attributes.description: Label for the aria-live region that announces removed tag(s) to screen reader users

attributes.name: tagValidator
attributes.description: Optional tag validator method. Passed a single argument of tag being added. Should return 'true' if the tag passes validation, or 'false' if the tag cannot be added

attributes.name: duplicateTagText
attributes.description: The message when duplicate tags are detected. Set to an empty string to disable the message

attributes.name: invalidTagText

attributes.name: separator
attributes.description: Separator character(s) that will trigger a tag to be created

attributes.name: removeOnDelete
attributes.description: When set, enables removal of last tag in tags when user presses delete or backspace and the input is empty

attributes.name: noAddOnEnter
attributes.description: When set, disables adding the tag on the input's 'keydown.enter' event

attributes.description: When set, disables the focus styling of the component root element

tags.name: BTags
tags.description:
Lightweight custom tagged input form control, with options for customized interface rendering, duplicate tag detection and optional tag validation

*Alias for BFormTags*

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: Used to set the 'id' attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

attributes.name: inputId
attributes.description: ID to apply to the new tag input element. If not provided, a unique ID will be auto generated

attributes.name: placeholder
attributes.description: Sets the 'placeholder' attribute value on the form control

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: When set to 'true', disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: Sets the value of the 'name' attribute on the form control. When set, creates a hidden input for each tag

attributes.name: form
attributes.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the 'form' attribute on the control

attributes.name: autofocus
attributes.description: When set to 'true', attempts to auto-focus the control when it is mounted, or re-activated when in a keep-alive. Does not set the 'autofocus' attribute on the control

attributes.name: state
attributes.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. 'true' for valid, 'false' for invalid', or 'null' for no validation state

attributes.name: size
attributes.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

attributes.name: inputType
attributes.description: Specifies the type of input to use: 'text', 'email', 'tel', 'url', or 'number'. Default is 'text'

attributes.name: inputClass
attributes.description: Class (or classes) to apply to the new tag input element

attributes.name: inputAttrs
attributes.description: Additional attributes to apply to the new tag input element

attributes.name: addButtonText
attributes.description: Text for the built in 'Add' button. Slot `add-button-text' takes precedence

attributes.name: addButtonVariant
attributes.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the 'Add' button

attributes.name: tagVariant
attributes.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the tags

attributes.name: tagClass
attributes.description: Class (or classes) to apply to the tags

attributes.name: tagPills
attributes.description: Makes the built in tags have a pill appearance

attributes.name: tagRemoveLabel
attributes.description: The value of the 'aria-label' attribute on the remove button in the tag

attributes.name: tagRemovedLabel
attributes.description: Label for the aria-live region that announces removed tag(s) to screen reader users

attributes.name: tagValidator
attributes.description: Optional tag validator method. Passed a single argument of tag being added. Should return 'true' if the tag passes validation, or 'false' if the tag cannot be added

attributes.name: duplicateTagText
attributes.description: The message when duplicate tags are detected. Set to an empty string to disable the message

attributes.name: invalidTagText
attributes.description: The error message when invalid tags are detected. Set to an empty string to disable the message

attributes.name: separator
attributes.description: Separator character(s) that will trigger a tag to be created

attributes.name: removeOnDelete
attributes.description: When set, enables removal of last tag in tags when user presses delete or backspace and the input is empty

attributes.name: addOnChange
attributes.description: When set, enables adding the tag on the input's 'change' event

attributes.name: noAddOnEnter
attributes.description: When set, disables adding the tag on the input's 'keydown.enter' event

attributes.name: noOuterFocus
attributes.description: When set, disables the focus styling of the component root element

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: Array of current tags. This is the v-model

events.name: input
events.description: Emitted when the tags changes. Updates the v-model

arguments.name: value
arguments.description: Array of current tags.

events.name: tag-state
events.description: Emitted when tags in the user input are parsed

arguments.name: validTags
arguments.description: Array of new tag(s) added (or that will be added). Will be zero length if no tags added.

arguments.name: invalidTags
arguments.description: Array of tag(s) that can not added because they did not pass validation. Will be zero length if no invalid tags.

arguments.name: duplicateTags
arguments.description: Array of tag(s) that can not added because they would be a duplicate tag. Will be zero length if no duplicate tags.

slots.name: add-button-text
slots.description: Content to place in the built in  'Add' button. Takes precedence over the 'add-button-text' prop. Not used when the default scoped slot is provided

slots.name: default
slots.description: Slot to override the default rendering of the tags component

tags.name: BFormTextarea
tags.description: Create multi-line text inputs with support for auto height sizing, minimum and maximum number of rows, and contextual validation states.

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: Used to set the 'id' attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: Sets the value of the 'name' attribute on the form control

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: When set to 'true', disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

attributes.name: required
attributes.description: Adds the 'required' attribute to the form control

attributes.name: form
attributes.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the 'form' attribute on the control

attributes.name: autofocus
attributes.description: When set to 'true', attempts to auto-focus the control when it is mounted, or re-activated when in a keep-alive. Does not set the 'autofocus' attribute on the control

attributes.name: size
attributes.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

attributes.name: state
attributes.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. 'true' for valid, 'false' for invalid', or 'null' for no validation state

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: The current value of the textarea. Result will always be a string, except when the 'number' prop is used

attributes.name: ariaInvalid
attributes.description: Sets the 'aria-invalid' attribute with the specified value

attributes.name: readonly
attributes.description: Sets the 'readonly' attribute on the form control

attributes.name: plaintext
attributes.description: Set the form control as readonly and renders the control to look like plain text (no borders)

attributes.name: autocomplete
attributes.description: Sets the 'autocomplete' attribute value on the form control

attributes.name: placeholder
attributes.description: Sets the 'placeholder' attribute value on the form control

attributes.name: formatter
attributes.description: reference to a function for formatting the textarea

attributes.name: lazyFormatter
attributes.description: When set, the textarea is formatted on blur instead of each keystroke (if there is a formatter specified)

attributes.name: trim
attributes.description: When set, trims any leading and trailing white space from the input value. Emulates the Vue '.trim' v-model modifier

attributes.name: number
attributes.description: When set attempts to convert the input value to a native number. Emulates the Vue '.number' v-model modifier

attributes.name: lazy
attributes.description: When set, updates the v-model on 'change'/'blur' events instead of 'input'. Emulates the Vue '.lazy' v-model modifier

attributes.name: debounce
attributes.description: When set to a number of milliseconds greater than zero, will debounce the user input. Has no effect if prop 'lazy' is set

attributes.name: rows
attributes.description: The minimum number of rows to display. Must be a value greater than 1

attributes.name: maxRows
attributes.description: The maximum number of rows to show. When provided, the textarea will grow (or shrink) to fit the content up to maximum rows

attributes.name: wrap
attributes.description: The value to place on the textarea's 'wrap' attribute. Controls how line break are returned

attributes.name: noResize
attributes.description: When set, disabled the browser's resize handle which prevents the user from changing the height of the textarea. Automatically set when in auto height mode

attributes.name: noAutoShrink
attributes.description: When set, prevents the auto height textarea from shrinking to fit the content

events.name: input
events.description: Input event triggered by user interaction. Emitted after any formatting (not including 'trim' or 'number' props) and after the v-model is updated

arguments.name: value
arguments.description: Current value of textarea

events.name: change
events.description: Change event triggered by user interaction. Emitted after any formatting (not including 'trim' or 'number' props) and after the v-model is updated.

arguments.name: value
arguments.description: Current value of the textarea

events.name: update
events.description: Emitted to update the v-model

arguments.name: value
arguments.description: Value of textarea, after any formatting. Not emitted if the value does nto change

events.name: blur
events.description: Emitted after the textarea looses focus

arguments.name: event
arguments.description: Native blur event (before any optional formatting occurs)

tags.name: BFormTimepicker
tags.description: BootstrapVue custom time picker input form control, which provides full WAI-ARIA accessibility (a11y) and supports internationalization (i18n)

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: Used to set the 'id' attribute on the rendered content, and used as the base to generate any additional element IDs as needed

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: Initially selected time value. Accepts a `HH:mm:ss` string. Valid value ranges from `00:00:00` to `23:59:59`

attributes.name: resetValue
attributes.description: When the optional `reset` button is clicked, the selected time will be set to this value. Default is to clear the selected value

attributes.name: placeholder
attributes.description: Text so show in the form control when no date is selected. Defaults to the `label-no-date-selected` prop value

attributes.name: size
attributes.description: Set the size of the component's appearance. 'sm', 'md' (default), or 'lg'

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: Places the timepicker in a non-interactive disabled state

attributes.name: readonly
attributes.description: Places the timepicker in an interactive readonly state. Disables updating the v-model, while still allowing focusing of spin buttons

attributes.name: required
attributes.description: When set, adds the `aria-required="true"` attribute on the component. Required validation needs to be handled by your application

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: Sets the value of the 'name' attribute on the form control

attributes.name: form
attributes.description: ID of the form that the form control belongs to. Sets the 'form' attribute on the control

attributes.name: state
attributes.description: Controls the validation state appearance of the component. 'true' for valid, 'false' for invalid', or 'null' for no validation state

attributes.name: hour12
attributes.description: Tri-state prop. If `true` forces the interface to 12 hour format. If `false` forces the interface into 24 hour format. If `null` the current locale will determine the 12 or 24 hour interface (default)

attributes.name: locale
attributes.description: Locale (or locales) for the component to use. When passing an array of locales, the order of the locales is from most preferred to least preferred. If not provided, defaults to the clients default locale

attributes.name: showSeconds
attributes.description: When true, shows the seconds spinbutton. If `false` the seconds spin button will not be shown and the seconds portion of the time will always be `0`

attributes.name: hideHeader
attributes.description: When set, visually hides the selected date header

attributes.name: secondsStep
attributes.description: Step value for the seconds spinbutton. Should be a value evenly divided into 60

attributes.name: minutesStep
attributes.description: Step value for the minutes spinbutton. Should be a value evenly divided into 60

attributes.name: buttonOnly
attributes.description: Renders the datepicker as a dropdown button instead of a form-control

attributes.name: buttonVariant
attributes.description: The button variant to use when in `button-only` mode. Has no effect if prop `button-only` is not set

attributes.name: nowButton
attributes.description: When set, shows the optional `select now` button

attributes.name: labelNowButton
attributes.description: Content for the optional `Select now` button

attributes.name: nowButtonVariant
attributes.description: Button variant to use for the optional `select today` button

attributes.name: resetButton
attributes.description: When set, shows the optional `reset` button

attributes.name: labelResetButton
attributes.description: Content for the optional `Reset` button

attributes.name: resetButtonVariant
attributes.description: Button variant to use for the optional `reset` button

attributes.name: noCloseButton
attributes.description: When set, disables showing the close button

attributes.name: labelCloseButton
attributes.description: Content for the `Close` button

attributes.name: closeButtonVariant
attributes.description: Button variant to use for the optional `close` button

attributes.name: labelSelected
attributes.description: Hidden sr-only string when a time is selected

attributes.name: labelNoTimeSelected
attributes.description: String to show when no time is selected

attributes.name: labelHours
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the `Hours` spinbutton

attributes.name: labelMinutes
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the `Minutes` spinbutton

attributes.name: labelSeconds
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the `Seconds` spinbutton

attributes.name: labelAmpm
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the `AM/PM` spinbutton

attributes.name: labelAm
attributes.description: Text to display in the AM/PM spinbutton when 'AM' is selected

attributes.name: labelPm
attributes.description: Text to display in the AM/PM spinbutton when 'PM' is selected

attributes.name: labelIncrement
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the spinbuttons `+` button

attributes.name: labelDecrement
attributes.description: Value of the `aria-label` attribute on the spinbuttons `-` button

attributes.name: menuClass
attributes.description: Class (or classes) to apply to to popup menu wrapper

attributes.name: dropup
attributes.description: When set, positions the menu on the top of the button

attributes.name: dropright
attributes.description: When set, positions the menu to the right of the button

attributes.name: dropleft
attributes.description: When set, positions the menu to the left of the button

attributes.name: right
attributes.description: Align the right edge of the menu with the right of the button

attributes.name: offset
attributes.description: Specify the number of pixels to shift the menu by. Negative values supported

attributes.name: noFlip
attributes.description: Prevent the menu from auto flipping positions

attributes.name: popperOpts
attributes.description: Additional configuration to pass to Popper.js

attributes.name: boundary
attributes.description: The boundary constraint of the menu: `'scrollParent'`, `'window'`, `'viewport'`, or a reference to an `HTMLElement`

events.name: input
events.description: Emitted when updating the v-model

arguments.name: time
arguments.description: A string in the format of `HH:mm:ss` (24 hour format)

events.name: context
events.description: `b-time` context event. Emitted when the user changes any spinbutton value via mouse or cursor control. Also emitted when the component is first instantiated, or the locale is changed

arguments.name: context
arguments.description: The `b-time` context object. See the `b-time` documentaion for details

events.name: shown
events.description: Emitted when the picker popup has shown

events.name: hidden
events.description: Emitted when the picker popup has hidden

slots.name: button-content
slots.description: Content to place in the timepicker's icon button

vue-properties.name: isHovered
vue-properties.description: `true` if the component is hovered

vue-properties.name: hasFocus
vue-properties.description: `true` if the timepicker icon button has focus

vue-properties.name: state
vue-properties.description: The value of the `state` prop. `true` (valid), `false` (invalid), or `null`

vue-properties.name: open
vue-properties.description: The visibility state of the popup. `true` if the popup is visible and `false` if not

attributes.name: tag

attributes.name: fill
attributes.description: Proportionately fills all horizontal space with nav items. All horizontal space is occupied, but not every nav item has the same width

attributes.name: justified
attributes.description: Fills all horizontal space with nav items, but unlike 'fill', every nav item will be the same width

attributes.name: align
attributes.description: Align the nav items in the nav: 'start' (or 'left'), 'center', 'end' (or 'right')

attributes.name: tabs
attributes.description: Renders the nav items with the appearance of tabs

attributes.name: pills
attributes.description: Renders the nav items with the appearance of pill buttons

attributes.name: vertical
attributes.description: Renders the nav vertically

attributes.name: small
attributes.description: Makes the nav smaller

attributes.name: cardHeader
attributes.description: Set this prop when the nav is placed inside a card header

tags.description: Navigation components that share general markup and styles, from the base <b-nav> class to the active and disabled states. Swap modifier props to switch between each style.

attributes.name: href
attributes.description: <b-link> prop: Denotes the target URL of the link for standard a links

attributes.name: rel
attributes.description: <b-link> prop: Sets the 'rel' attribute on the rendered link

attributes.name: target
attributes.description: <b-link> prop: Sets the 'target' attribute on the rendered link

attributes.name: active
attributes.description: When set to 'true', places the component in the active state with active styling

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: When set to 'true', disables the component's functionality and places it in a disabled state

attributes.name: to
attributes.description: <router-link> prop: Denotes the target route of the link. When clicked, the value of the to prop will be passed to router.push() internally, so the value can be either a string or a Location descriptor object

attributes.name: append
attributes.description: <router-link> prop: Setting append prop always appends the relative path to the current path

attributes.name: replace
attributes.description: <router-link> prop: Setting the replace prop will call 'router.replace()' instead of 'router.push()' when clicked, so the navigation will not leave a history record

attributes.name: activeClass
attributes.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

attributes.name: exact
attributes.description: <router-link> prop: The default active class matching behavior is inclusive match. Setting this prop forces the mode to exactly match the route

attributes.name: exactActiveClass
attributes.description: <router-link> prop: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact match. Typically you will want to set this to class name 'active'

attributes.name: prefetch
attributes.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting 'prefetch' to 'true' or 'false' will overwrite the default value of 'router.prefetchLinks'

attributes.name: noPrefetch
attributes.description: <nuxt-link> prop: To improve the responsiveness of your Nuxt.js applications, when the link will be displayed within the viewport, Nuxt.js will automatically prefetch the code splitted page. Setting 'no-prefetch' will disabled this feature for the specific link

attributes.name: routerComponentName
attributes.description: <b-link> prop: BootstrapVue auto detects between `<router-link>` and `<nuxt-link>`. In cases where you want to use a 3rd party link component based on `<router-link>`, set this prop to the component name. e.g. set it to 'g-link' if you are using Gridsome (note only `<router-link>` specific props are passed to the component)

attributes.name: linkAttrs
attributes.description: Additional attributes to place on the nested link element

attributes.name: linkClasses
attributes.description: CSS class (or classes) to place on the nested link element

For simple display of tabular data without all the fancy features, BootstrapVue also provides lightweight alternative components <b-table-lite> and <b-table-simple>

attributes.description: Array of items to display, or an items provider function reference. Refer to the docs for details

attributes.description: Set to true to sort the column in descending order. Syncable with the .sync prop modifier

attributes.description: The initial sorting direction to sort an unsorted column by: 'asc', 'desc', or 'last' (to use the previous sort direction)

attributes.description: The locale string (or array of locale string) that specified the language when sorting. See docs for details

attributes.name: labelSortDesc

attributes.name: noFooterSorting

tags.name: BIcon
tags.description: Bootstrap Icons are designed to work with Bootstrap components, from form controls to navigation. Bootstrap Icons are SVGs, so they scale quickly and easily and can be styled with CSS.

attributes.name: icon
attributes.description: Name of icon to render. The corresponding icon component must be installed

attributes.name: variant
attributes.description: Contextual color variant. By default the icon inherits the current text color

attributes.name: fontScale
attributes.description: Scale the icons current font size

attributes.name: scale
attributes.description: Scales the icon's SVG, without increasing the font size

attributes.name: rotate
attributes.description: Rotates the icon by the specified number of degrees. Positive values rotate clockwise, while negative values rotate counterclockwise

attributes.name: flipH
attributes.description: Flips the icon horizontally

attributes.name: flipV
attributes.description: Flips the icon vertically

attributes.name: shiftH
attributes.description: Moves the icon horizontally. Positive numbers will shift the icon right, negative left. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: shiftV
attributes.description: Moves the icon vertically. Positive numbers will shift the icon up, negative down. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: animation
attributes.description: Animate the icon. Supported built-in animations are 'cylon', 'fade', 'pulse', 'spin' and 'throb'

attributes.name: stacked
attributes.description: Set this prop to true when placing inside a BIconstack component

attributes.description: Contextual color variant. By default the icon inherits the current text color

attributes.name: fontScale
attributes.description: Scale the icons current font size

attributes.name: scale
attributes.description: Scales the icon's SVG, without increasing the font size

attributes.name: rotate
attributes.description: Rotates the icon by the specified number of degrees. Positive values rotate clockwise, while negative values rotate counterclockwise

attributes.name: flipH
attributes.description: Flips the icon horizontally

attributes.name: flipV
attributes.description: Flips the icon vertically

attributes.name: shiftH
attributes.description: Moves the icon horizontally. Positive numbers will shift the icon right, negative left. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: shiftV
attributes.description: Moves the icon vertically. Positive numbers will shift the icon up, negative down. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: animation
attributes.description: Animate the icon. Supported built-in animations are 'cylon', 'fade', 'pulse', 'spin' and 'throb'

attributes.name: stacked
attributes.description: Set this prop to true when placing inside a BIconstack component

attributes.description: Contextual color variant. By default the icon inherits the current text color

attributes.name: fontScale
attributes.description: Scale the icons current font size

attributes.name: scale
attributes.description: Scales the icon's SVG, without increasing the font size

attributes.name: rotate
attributes.description: Rotates the icon by the specified number of degrees. Positive values rotate clockwise, while negative values rotate counterclockwise

attributes.name: flipH
attributes.description: Flips the icon horizontally

attributes.name: flipV
attributes.description: Flips the icon vertically

attributes.name: shiftH
attributes.description: Moves the icon horizontally. Positive numbers will shift the icon right, negative left. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: shiftV
attributes.description: Moves the icon vertically. Positive numbers will shift the icon up, negative down. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: animation
attributes.description: Animate the icon. Supported built-in animations are 'cylon', 'fade', 'pulse', 'spin' and 'throb'

attributes.name: stacked
attributes.description: Set this prop to true when placing inside a BIconstack component

attributes.description: Flips the icon horizontally

attributes.description: Flips the icon vertically

attributes.name: stacked
attributes.description: Set this prop to true when placing inside a BIconstack component

attributes.description: Contextual color variant. By default the icon inherits the current text color

attributes.name: fontScale
attributes.description: Scale the icons current font size

attributes.name: scale
attributes.description: Scales the icon's SVG, without increasing the font size

attributes.name: rotate
attributes.description: Rotates the icon by the specified number of degrees. Positive values rotate clockwise, while negative values rotate counterclockwise

attributes.name: flipH
attributes.description: Flips the icon horizontally

attributes.name: flipV
attributes.description: Flips the icon vertically

attributes.name: shiftH
attributes.description: Moves the icon horizontally. Positive numbers will shift the icon right, negative left. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: shiftV
attributes.description: Moves the icon vertically. Positive numbers will shift the icon up, negative down. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: animation
attributes.description: Animate the icon. Supported built-in animations are 'cylon', 'fade', 'pulse', 'spin' and 'throb'

attributes.name: stacked
attributes.description: Set this prop to true when placing inside a BIconstack component

attributes.name: fontScale
attributes.description: Scale the icons current font size

attributes.name: scale
attributes.description: Scales the icon's SVG, without increasing the font size

attributes.name: rotate
attributes.description: Rotates the icon by the specified number of degrees. Positive values rotate clockwise, while negative values rotate counterclockwise

attributes.name: flipH
attributes.description: Flips the icon horizontally

attributes.name: flipV
attributes.description: Flips the icon vertically

attributes.name: shiftH
attributes.description: Moves the icon horizontally. Positive numbers will shift the icon right, negative left. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: shiftV
attributes.description: Moves the icon vertically. Positive numbers will shift the icon up, negative down. Value is in 1/16em units

attributes.name: animation
attributes.description: Animate the icon. Supported built-in animations are 'cylon', 'fade', 'pulse', 'spin' and 'throb'

attributes.name: stacked
attributes.description: Set this prop to true when placing inside a BIconstack component

attributes.name: v-b-modal
attributes.description: Modals are streamlined, but flexible dialog prompts powered by JavaScript and CSS. They support a number of use cases from user notification to completely custom content and feature a handful of helpful sub-components, sizes, variants, accessibility, and more.

vue-modifiers.name: {modalId}
vue-modifiers.description: Modal ID to open. Replace `{modalId}` with the modal's ID

attributes.name: v-b-hover
attributes.description: A lightweight directive that allows you to react when an element either becomes hovered or unhovered

attributes.name: v-b-popover
attributes.description: Add BootstrapVue popovers to any element on your site, using Bootstrap v4 CSS for styling and animations. Popovers are tooltips on steroids.

vue-argument.description: ID of element to append the popover markup when visible. Optional, defaults to the body

vue-modifiers.name: top
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the top of the trigger element (default)

vue-modifiers.name: right
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the right of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: bottom
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the bottom of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: auto
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover in the best fit place around the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: topright
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the top-right of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: topleft
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the top-left of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: bottomright
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the bottom-right of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: bottomleft
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the bottom-left of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: lefttop
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the left-top of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: leftbottom
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the left-bottom of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: righttop
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the right-top of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: rightbottom
vue-modifiers.description: Positions the popover on the right-bottom of the trigger element

vue-modifiers.name: nofade
vue-modifiers.description: Disabled the fade animation of the popover

vue-modifiers.name: html
vue-modifiers.description: Enables basic HTML in the title/content (use with caution)

vue-modifiers.name: viewport
vue-modifiers.description: Sets the boundary constraint to the viewport

vue-modifiers.name: window
vue-modifiers.description: sets the boundary constrain to the window

vue-modifiers.name: v-{variant}
vue-modifiers.description: Sets the popover contextual color variant to `{variant}`

vue-modifiers.name: d{###}
vue-modifiers.description: The show and hide delay in milliseconds (where `{###}` is the value in milliseconds)

vue-modifiers.name: ds{###}
vue-modifiers.description: The show delay in milliseconds (where `{###}` is the value in milliseconds)

vue-modifiers.name: dh{###}
vue-modifiers.description: The hide delay in milliseconds (where `{###}` is the value in milliseconds)

vue-modifiers.name: o{###}
vue-modifiers.description: An offset value in pixels (where `{###}` is the number of pixels, defaults to 0. Negative values allowed)

attributes.name: v-b-scrollspy
attributes.description: Automatically activate BootstrapVue navigation or list group components based on scroll position to indicate which link is currently active in the viewport.

vue-argument.description: ID of element to monitor scrolling on (if not provided defaults to the body element)

vue-modifiers.description: Offset (in pixels) from top of scrolling viewport before triggering active state

vue-modifiers.name: offset
vue-modifiers.description: Position calculation method using `offset` procedure (default process for body)

vue-modifiers.name: position
vue-modifiers.description: Position calculation method using the `position` procedure

vue-modifiers.name: auto
vue-modifiers.description: Position calculation method: `auto` will choose `offset` if scroll element is body, else the method is `position`. This is the default.

attributes.name: v-b-toggle
attributes.description: A light-weight directive for toggling visibility state for collapses and sidebars by ID. It automatically handles the accessibility attributes on the trigger element.

vue-modifiers.name: {componentId}
vue-modifiers.description: ID of component to toggle
